READ ME

Steps to run the automation script:


The tests is wriiten using selenium webdriver and java, with junit framework in Page Object Model.

Download the zip file 'OracleTest.zip' and unzip it.

Required softwares- Google Chrome webrowser, Eclipse IDE, and java jdk 1.8 installed on the system.

Java can be downloaded from here: https://java.com/en/download/

Selenium jar file can downloaded from here: https://www.seleniumhq.org/download/

Chrome browser can be downloaded from here: https://www.google.com/chrome/

Eclipse IDE can be downloaded from here: https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/

Download 'chromedriver.exe' file from this link: http://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads


Open Eclipse IDE-> click on File -> Click on Import -> select General - Existing Projects into Workspace and click Next-> in Select root directory, click browse and select the unziped file 'OracleTest' and click on Finish Button.

Run the Tests.java as junit.


The test results can be seen in the console of the eclipse IDE.